I"(<p><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2017/aug/08/public-libraries-at-the-crossroads-should-volunteers-be-keeping-them-open">Not just because by “stepping in” you’re speeding up the end of libraries</a>, nor because of any notion of professionalism. No — volunteer–run libraries are an experiment in a mean, barebones state, testing how far governments can go in divesting themselves of any responsibility or cost. They’re a softer target than, say, adult care, but they’re the <em>first</em> target, the first justification.</p>
